 observed phylogenetic conflicts arise from both gene tree error and deep incomplete lineage sorting. In addition to resolving long-standing inconsistencies in the reported relationships among major lineages, we show that Old World fruit bats have likely undergone at least seven independent dietary transitions from frugivory to nectarivory. Finally, we use this phylogeny to identify and describe one new genus. [Chiroptera; coalescence; concordance; incomplete lineage sorting; nectar feeder; species tree; target enrichment.]", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Nesi, Nicolas", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tsagkogeorga, Georgia", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tsang, Susan M", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Nicolas, Violaine", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lalis, Aude", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Scanlon, Annette T", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Riesle-Sbarbaro, Silke A", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Wiantoro, Sigit", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hitch, Alan T", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Juste, Javier", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pinzari, Corinna A", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bonaccorso, Frank J", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Todd, Christopher M", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lim, Burton K", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Simmons, Nancy B", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "McGowen, Michael R", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Rossiter, Stephen J", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Davalos, Liliana", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Animals", "Biological Evolution", "Chiroptera", "Evolution, Molecular", "Phylogeny", "Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/c529406cc6f7d1df552b061dd1e5b85d", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/18011375ac6cd40162f66216f397f599ba22cc5c13dac9a8737efe7005b6fa0a", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/543554